Initially, event1 happened. After event2, either event1, or event3 must happen. After event1, event2 must happen. After event3, event1 must happen.

=== Hypothesis ===

C1: Event1 does not happen.
C2: C1 always holds.

C2 is True or False?
graph:
<graphml xmlns="http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns/1.0/graphml.xsd">
  <graph edgedefault="directed">
    <node id="event1" />
    <node id="event2" />
    <node id="event3" />
    <edge source="event1" target="event2" />
    <edge source="event2" target="event1" />
    <edge source="event2" target="event3" />
    <edge source="event3" target="event1" />
  </graph>
</graphml>
prediction_raw:
Step 1 — identify hypothesis
- C1: "Event1 does not happen."
- C2: "C1 always holds" (i.e., event1 never happens at any time).

Step 2 — examine given facts/rules
- Initially, event1 happened. (Directly contradicts C1 right away.)
- Also: after event1, event2 must happen; after event2, either event1 or event3 must happen; after event3, event1 must happen. Those rules in fact ensure event1 recurs, but that's extra — the initial fact already suffices.

Step 3 — conclusion
- Because event1 happened initially, C1 is false at that time, so C1 does not always hold. Therefore C2 ("C1 always holds") is false.

Final answer: False
